@Barry Ancona - On ships, the things made out of rope are usually, but not always, called lines. There are exceptions -- tiller rope, bell rope, etc. 

The material that is used to make lines is called rope. A lot of mariners get this wrong, and will correct you if you call a rope a rope. They are wrong.

I always just tell them to head down to the Rope House at Mystic Seaport and tell them that they aren't making rope and need to change all their education materials about how rope is made.

